---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Iron Conclave - Enemy Forces"
  description="Meet the Iron Conclave: Duergar and Orc forces occupying Amn. Learn about High Forgemaster Tharûm Blackmantle and the enemies you'll face in Operation Golden Sword."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <p class="section-title">Know Your Enemy</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">The Iron Conclave</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        A militarized alliance of Duergar and Orc War-Clans, united under a single, merciless doctrine.
        This is not a raiding force — this is an occupation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- High Forgemaster -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-start">
          <!-- Image -->
          <div class="md:col-span-1">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
              <img
                src="/images/High_Forgemaster_Blackmantle.jpg"
                alt="High Forgemaster Tharûm Blackmantle"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="md:col-span-2">
            <p class="section-title">Supreme Commander</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display text-dnd-secondary mb-2">
              High Forgemaster Tharûm Blackmantle
            </h2>
            <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm mb-6">Duergar Warlord / Artificer / Warlock</p>

            <div class="space-y-4 text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Tharûm Blackmantle rose from the brutal politics of the Underdark, where survival depended
                not on strength, but on calculation. His clan was abandoned by its allies during a territorial
                collapse, teaching him a lesson he never forgot: <strong class="text-dnd-text">morality is
                irrelevant without leverage.</strong>
              </p>
              <p>
                From that moment on, Tharûm devoted himself not to conquest, but to inevitability—learning
                siegecraft, logistics, and the economics of war until domination became a matter of planning
                rather than chance.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong class="text-dnd-text">Amn was chosen not out of hatred, but efficiency.</strong> Its
                wealth, guilds, and trade networks make it the perfect engine for continental conquest.
                Through enslaved elementals, bound fiends, and shadow-forged engines, Tharûm wages war as
                an industry, believing resistance only prolongs suffering.
              </p>
              <p class="text-dnd-secondary italic">
                He does not seek glory or loyalty—only stability enforced by overwhelming advantage.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Warmagus -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-start">
          <!-- Content (reversed order on desktop) -->
          <div class="md:col-span-2 md:order-1">
            <p class="section-title">Keeper of the Coastal Keep</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display text-theater-portals mb-2">
              The Warmagus
            </h2>
            <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm mb-6">Conclave Archmage / Strategic Commander</p>

            <div class="space-y-4 text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Once a respected Amnian arcane scholar, the Warmagus specialized in long-range communication
                and battlefield coordination. When Athkatla fell, they chose not to flee, believing resistance
                would only fracture the realm further.
              </p>
              <p>
                Instead, they offered their expertise to the Iron Conclave, convinced that
                <strong class="text-dnd-text">a swift, orderly conquest would spare the greatest number of lives.</strong>
              </p>
              <p>
                From the Coastal Keep, the Warmagus maintains the arcane relay linking Athkatla to the eastern
                armies—synchronizing ground, air, and siege forces with ruthless precision.
              </p>
              <p>
                Knowing they are a single point of failure, they developed a forbidden contingency:
                <strong class="text-dnd-text">fracturing their consciousness into multiple autonomous arcane aspects.</strong>
                To the Warmagus, this is not madness, but responsibility—command divided so it cannot be
                destroyed in a single blow.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Image -->
          <div class="md:col-span-1 md:order-2">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
              <img
                src="/images/The_Warmagus.jpg"
                alt="The Warmagus"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Faction: Blackmantle Duergar -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-start">
          <!-- Image -->
          <div class="md:col-span-1">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
              <img
                src="/images/Blackmantle_Duergar.jpg"
                alt="The Blackmantle Duergar"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="md:col-span-2">
            <p class="section-title">Faction</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">
              The Blackmantle Duergar
            </h2>
            <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm mb-6">Architects of the War Machine</p>

            <div class="space-y-4 text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <p>
                Elite duergar clans bound directly to Tharûm Blackmantle by oath, contract, or pact.
                They serve as engineers, logisticians, overseers, and commanders.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong class="text-dnd-text">They view war as an industrial process to be optimized,
                not a struggle to be glorified.</strong> Waste is considered failure. They enslave
                conquered populations for labor, not cruelty.
              </p>
              <p>
                They believe surface realms are decadent, inefficient, and unworthy of autonomy.
                They speak openly of Amn as a "resource basin," not a kingdom.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-3">Duergar Tactics</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-dnd-secondary">⚙️</span>
                  <span>Siege engines powered by enslaved fire elementals</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-dnd-secondary">⚙️</span>
                  <span>Shadow-forged weapons and armor</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-dnd-secondary">⚙️</span>
                  <span>Rigid formations and overlapping fields of fire</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6">
              <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-3">Common Roles</h4>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Forge-priests</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">War-artificers</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Siege overseers</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Battery commanders</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg-secondary border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Intelligence officers</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Faction: Orc War-Clans -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-start">
          <!-- Content (reversed order on desktop) -->
          <div class="md:col-span-2 md:order-1">
            <p class="section-title">Faction</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-display text-dnd-text mb-2">
              The Orc War-Clans
            </h2>
            <p class="text-dnd-primary text-sm mb-6">The Hammer Behind the Anvil</p>

            <div class="space-y-4 text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <p>
                A coalition of orc clans shattered by years of internecine warfare, united under Tharûm
                through conquest, coercion, and promised plunder.
              </p>
              <p>
                They serve as shock troops, vanguard forces, and occupation enforcers. Given freedom to
                fight as they wish—<strong class="text-dnd-text">so long as objectives are met.</strong>
              </p>
              <p>
                Conditioned to believe that service to the Conclave leads to endless war and spoils.
                <strong class="text-dnd-secondary">Many are unaware they are considered expendable by
                duergar leadership.</strong>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card bg-dnd-bg">
              <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-3">Orc Tactics</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-dnd-secondary">⚔️</span>
                  <span>Brutal frontal assaults</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-dnd-secondary">⚔️</span>
                  <span>Boarding actions and beach charges</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-dnd-secondary">⚔️</span>
                  <span>Overwhelming numbers and relentless pressure</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6">
              <h4 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-3">Common Roles</h4>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Beach assault infantry</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Heavy shock units</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Berserkers</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Aerial beast riders</span>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded text-sm text-dnd-text-muted">Boarding parties</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Image -->
          <div class="md:col-span-1 md:order-2">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-dnd-bg border border-dnd-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
              <img
                src="/images/Orc_War-Clans.jpg"
                alt="The Orc War-Clans"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tharûm's Control -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-dnd-primary mb-6">The Balance of Power</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-3">Duergar Bonds</h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Bound by contracts, doctrine, and ideology. They serve because the system profits them.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-text mb-3">Orc Bonds</h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Bound by fear, momentum, and reward. They serve because they know nothing else.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-dnd-secondary/10 border-dnd-secondary">
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-4">
            Neither faction trusts the other—but both fear Tharûm's reprisal. The Coastal Keep exists
            primarily to ensure orc aggression is properly directed, duergar command is never isolated,
            and neither side can rebel without being crushed by the other.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="text-dnd-secondary font-display text-lg italic">
            "The clans fight because they must. The forges burn because they profit.<br/>
            I rule because the system functions."
          </blockquote>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm mt-2">— Tharûm Blackmantle</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">Ready to Face Them?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Now that you know your enemy, choose your theater and join the fight to break the Iron Conclave's grip.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-primary">Sign Up Now</a>
        <a href="/story" class="btn btn-secondary">Read the Full Story</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
